Airline Visual Identity 1945-1975 revisits a time when the skies were dominated by Pan Am, British Overseas Airways Corp (BOAC) and Continental . 
  The adverts were created for the biggest airlines of the day and promote destinations such as New York and London . 
  Book contains dozens of glamorous adverts from the golden age of air travel . 
  Airline Visual identity 1945- 1975 is a 436-page coffee table book . 
 